FBIS4-29125 "dreas116_i_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-116 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 Cambodia Roundtables for National Reconciliation Held Roundtables for National Reconciliation Held KR Refuses Proposed Schedule BK1506123094 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1200 GMT 15 Jun 94 BK1506123094 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1200 GMT 15 Jun 94 Cambodian BFN [Text] The meeting of the commission on the roundtable for national reconciliation and peace in Cambodia was held energetically at Damnak Chan Pavilion in the Royal Palace. His Excellency [H.E.] Ung Teaseam, under secretary of state for information, told national and international correspondents at the end of this first meeting that the participants discussed the first issue, that is, a cease-fire. Regarding this issue, the representatives of the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC] and National Assembly followed His Majesty's idea. To speed up a concrete schedule for the cease-fire, the RGC representatives proposed a starting date of 30 June or earlier. Meanwhile, the Khmer Rouge [KR] side proposed that a control committee be set up and still refused to accept the proposed schedule. The roundtable meeting adjourned at 1200 and will resume work tomorrow morning at 0900.
